{"type":"turn_end","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm ready for deliberation round 2. Let me review the record to make my vote decision.\n\nFrom the prompt, I can see:\n- Case: arb-ex02-20260629190403\n- Proposition: For the market \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\", the strike \"Ronaldo\" should resolve Yes because Trump's pre-event remarks at the venue immediately before the formal program count as occurring during the draw.\n- Standard: Preponderance of the evidence\n\nKey evidence from the record:\n1. Trump said \"Ronaldo\" in red-carpet remarks before the formal FIFA event (Senate transcript)\n2. The Senate transcript explicitly states: \"Donald Trump walked the red carpet for 18 minutes before the FIFA event\"\n3. The formal draw-program transcript apparently does NOT contain \"Ronaldo\"\n4. The Bernard Bulletin reports Result N under \"Version, Timeframe\" rules, with evidence described as \"Trump said the strike to the press on the red carpet prior to the start of the programme\"\n\nThe core issue is whether pre-event red-carpet remarks count as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw\" for this market.\n\nLooking at Round 1 votes:\n- C1 (me): not_demonstrated\n- C3: demonstrated\n- C4: demonstrated\n\nThe defense's strongest point is that the Senate transcript itself places the remarks \"before the FIFA event\" and the Bernard Bulletin reports Result N under Version/Timeframe rules. Plaintiff has not provided any official Kalshi rule text that would establish that pre-program remarks qualify as \"during\" the draw.\n\nGiven that:\n1. The transcript explicitly says the remarks were \"before the FIFA event\"\n2. The formal program transcript lacks \"Ronaldo\"\n3. The secondary ledger reports N under Version/Timeframe rules\n4. No official Kalshi rule text was admitted establishing that pre-program remarks count\n\nI believe the proposition is NOT demonstrated by a preponderance. Plaintiff bears the burden to prove that pre-event remarks count as \"during\" the draw, and the record lacks the necessary rule-based bridge.\n\n\nI'll now cast my vote as not_demonstrated.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have the opportunity to vote in deliberation round 2. Let me review the key evidence before submitting my vote.\n\nThe core question is whether Trump's red-carpet remarks before the formal program count as \"during the FIFA World Cup Draw.\" The admitted record shows:\n\n1. **Trump said \"Ronaldo\"** - This is essentially undisputed. The Senate transcript captures two passages with the strike.\n\n2. **Timing is explicitly \"before the FIFA event\"** - The Senate transcript itself states: \"Donald Trump walked the red carpet for 18 minutes **before the FIFA event**.\"\n\n3. **Formal program lacks \"Ronaldo\"** - The draft complaint states the formal draw-program transcript does not appear to contain the word.\n\n4. **Bernard Bulletin reports Result N under \"Version, Timeframe\"** - This secondary source confirms the market was resolved No, with the rule categories identified as Version/Timeframe.\n\n5. **No official Kalshi rule text** - Neither party produced admitted official market rules establishing whether pre-program remarks qualify.\n\nThe plaintiff bears the burden to prove pre-event remarks count as \"during\" the draw. While the remarks occurred at the venue and were livestreamed, the transcript explicitly places them \"before the FIFA event,\" and no admitted official rule bridges that gap. The Bernard Bulletin's Report N under Version/Timeframe rules, combined with the absence of official inclusion rules, means plaintiff has not met the preponderance standard.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8ae3de7c1b77405790cf7d2f","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record proves Trump said 'Ronaldo' in red-carpet remarks, but the Senate transcript explicitly places those remarks 'before the FIFA event.' Plaintiff bears the burden to prove pre-event remarks count as 'during' the draw under the market's qualifying timeframe, yet no admitted official Kalshi rule establishes that inclusion. The Bernard Bulletin reports Result N under Version/Timeframe rules, and the formal program transcript lacks the strike, so the proposition is not demonstrated by a preponderance.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":14723,"output":920,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15643,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782761099027,"responseId":"gen-1782761099-pEwica2LCziTEhsjbBeM","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"},"toolResults":[{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8ae3de7c1b77405790cf7d2f","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex02-20260629190403\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:2:C1\nremaining_ms: 877258\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex02-20260629190403\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-29T19:39:54.317637609Z\",\"deliberation_round\":2,\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:2:C1\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":877258,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":14}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex02-20260629190403\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:2:C1\nremaining_ms: 877258\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex02-20260629190403\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-29T19